    "severity": "critical",
    "description": "Missing token expiry validation for delegation tokens. The tokenExpiryTimestamp is retrieved and stored but is never validated to check whether the token has expired (System.currentTimeMillis() > tokenExpiryTimestamp). This allows expired delegation tokens to be accepted during authentication, enabling token replay attacks and access by users whose credentials should have expired.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/security/scram/internals/ScramSaslServer.java
+++ b/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/security/scram/internals/ScramSaslServer.java
@@ -118,6 +118,8 @@
                             credentialCallback = tokenCallback;
                             callbackHandler.handle(new Callback[]{nameCallback, tokenCallback});
                             if (tokenCallback.tokenOwner() == null)
                                 throw new SaslException("Token Authentication failed: Invalid tokenId : " + username);
                             this.authorizationId = tokenCallback.tokenOwner();
                             this.tokenExpiryTimestamp = tokenCallback.tokenExpiryTimestamp();
+                            if (tokenExpiryTimestamp != null && System.currentTimeMillis() > tokenExpiryTimestamp)
+                                throw new SaslException("Delegation token has expired");
                         } else {
                             credentialCallback = new ScramCredentialCallback();
                             callbackHandler.handle(new Callback[]{nameCallback, credentialCallback});
"
  },
  {
    "file": "core/src/main/scala/kafka/security/authorizer/AclAuthorizer.scala",
    "line": 377,
    "severity": "critical",
    "description": "Authorization bypass in authorizeByResourceType method. The check for shouldAllowEveryoneIfNoAclIsFound returns ALLOWED before examining denyPrefixes and allow ACLs, violating the principle that DENY ACLs should always take precedence. A principal with matching deny prefix ACLs could be granted access if this config is enabled, bypassing authorization controls.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/core/src/main/scala/kafka/security/authorizer/AclAuthorizer.scala
+++ b/core/src/main/scala/kafka/security/authorizer/AclAuthorizer.scala
@@ -372,10 +372,6 @@
     if (denyAll(denyLiterals)) {
       logAuditMessage(requestContext, action, authorized = false)
       return AuthorizationResult.DENIED
     }
-
-    if (shouldAllowEveryoneIfNoAclIsFound) {
-      logAuditMessage(requestContext, action, authorized = true)
-      return AuthorizationResult.ALLOWED
-    }

     val denyPrefixes = matchingResources(
       resourceSnapshot, principalStr, host, op, AclPermissionType.DENY, resourceType, PatternType.PREFIXED)
@@ -400,7 +396,10 @@
     } else {
       logAuditMessage(requestContext, action, authorized = false)
       return AuthorizationResult.DENIED
     }
+
+    if (shouldAllowEveryoneIfNoAclIsFound) {
+      logAuditMessage(requestContext, action, authorized = true)
+      return AuthorizationResult.ALLOWED
+    }

     val allowLiterals = matchingResources(
       resourceSnapshot, principalStr, host, op, AclPermissionType.ALLOW, resourceType, PatternType.LITERAL)
"
  }
]

